</i></a></div><div class="clearfix"></div></div></div>
<div class="content-data"><div id="list-content-mobile" class="hidden-md hidden-lg"></div><div class="lesson-tab" role="tabpanel"><ul class="nav nav-tabs" role="tablist"><li role="presentation" class="active"><a href="#about" aria-controls="about" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Course details</a></li><li role="presentation"><a href="#transcript" aria-controls="transcript" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Transcript</a></li><li role="presentation"><a href="#pattern" aria-controls="pattern" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Pattern</a></li><li role="presentation"><a href="#diploma" aria-controls="transcript" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Diploma</a></li><li role="presentation"><a class="faq-tab blank" href="#faq" aria-controls="faq" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">FAQs</a></li></ul><div class="tab-content"><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane active" id="about"><div class="dark-get-started margin-0"><div class="demo-slider"><h4 class="text-center">Garments you can make using this technology:</h4><div id="amazingcarousel-container"><div id="amazingcarousel" style="display:none"><div class="amazingcarousel-list-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-list-wrapper"><ul class="amazingcarousel-list"><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5737.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5737.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5840.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5840.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5943.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5943.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5991.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5991.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6027.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6027.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6045.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6045.jpg" alt=""> </a></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li></ul></div><div class="amazingcarousel-prev"></div><div class="amazingcarousel-next"></div></div></div></div></div><p><strong>The popularity of this model among brides is because it reflects almost all following fashion trends:</strong></p><ul><li>a delicate elastic top with embroidery;</li><li>a built-in bra or cut-off cups;</li><li>a tender silhouette of a lace dress;</li><li>an open back and a short lacing on air loops;</li><li>and a full detachable skirt with a train.</li></ul><p><strong>This course contains a lot of couture techniques. I will show you the following:</strong></p><ul><li>how to seamlessly cover the corset with lace;</li><li>how to join a lace folded skirt to a dress, so that you don’t have any extra thickness and the transition from a corset to a dress is smooth and invisible;</li><li>how to sew an elastic top between a face and a lining;</li><li>how to make a lining with built-in cups.</li></ul><p><strong>The special feature of the course is tambour (luneville) sequin embroidery.</strong></p><p>The process of cutting, sewing and decoration of a garment from scratch to final operations is described and illustrated in detail.<br> All necessary patterns and bonuses (for printing) are attached as follows:</p><ul><li>2 tables for AUTOMATIC pattern adjustments calculation for all patterns of this course;</li><li>patterns of a corset face and a corset lining;</li><li>patterns of decorative details.</li></ul><div><p><strong>The aim of the course</strong>&nbsp;is my great desire to teach the techniques of making such dresses. All the techniques can be used in various combinations, so that you can sew different models of evening, cocktail, prom and wedding dresses.</p><p><strong>The course is useful</strong>&nbsp;both to beginners as well as to experienced professionals in making wedding and evening dresses. It can be handy for dressmaking atelier personnel as a professional development training.</p></div><div></div><div><p><strong>Author:</strong>&nbsp;Tatiana Kozorovitsky</p><p><strong>Total length:</strong>&nbsp;5h 00m</p></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="transcript"><div class="overlay"></div><div itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"> <span itemprop="publisher" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Organization"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy"> <span itemprop="logo" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="text" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="https://www.facebook.com/corsetacademy"> </span> <span itemprop="author" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tatiana Kozorovitsky"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="width" content="128"><meta itemprop="height" content="128"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/jpeg"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/author/infocorsetacademy-net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="http://www.corsetacademy.net"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-54-preparation-for-final-decoration-of-the-top/"><meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-54-preparation-for-final-decoration-of-the-top/"><meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-12-05T22:03:24+00:00"><meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2018-12-05T22:03:24+00:00"><meta itemprop="copyrightYear" content="2018"><meta itemprop="inLanguage" content="en_US"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tutorial 54. Preparation for final decoration of the top."><meta itemprop="headline" content="Tutorial 54. Preparation for final decoration of the top."><meta itemprop="description" content="The dress-fitting shows that the mock-up of our top fits well. Thus, I checked the pattern and finally get assured that it is possible to cut the main top"><meta itemprop="articleSection" content="Wedding Dress with Detachable Full Skirt. Part 2."><meta itemprop="keywords" content="wedding dress with detachable full skirt. part 2., video"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><div itemprop="articleBody"><h1>Tutorial 54. Preparation for final decoration of the top.</h1><p><strong>The dress-fitting shows that the mock-up of our top fits well. </strong>Thus, I checked the pattern and finally get assured that it is possible to cut the main top. During the dress-fitting there appeared minor issues to alter the back and I would tell about them later when I would do alterations into the pattern.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2054.files/image002.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>The top of our dress will be sewn from white illusion mesh fabric. </strong>This is the high quality fine mesh fabric. Although, it has two major disadvantages: firstly, it is not easily available and secondly, this mesh fabric is super elastic in all directions and that means it is extremely difficult to embroider on it.</p><p><strong>So, I recommend especially to the beginners to use soft and tender euro mesh fabric or euro tulle. </strong>Atl least, euro tulle is stretchable only in one direction and it is easier to place into embroidery frame than illusion mesh fabric. Please remember that euro tulle in embroidery frame need to be placed so that the stretching side goes from the top to the bottom of the top and non-stretching side goes in width.</p><p><strong>So, what have I done to trace the top mock-up onto the real fabric? </strong></p><p><strong>On a soft plate I place our initial pattern, which we used to trace the contours of our embroidery elements, and I cover it with cellophane.&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p><p>Then <strong>I place the illusion mesh fabric in such a way, </strong>so the raw edge of fabric goes from top to bottom along vertical line and the cut of fabric goes along horizontal line<strong>. </strong></p><p><strong>The lower part of top is pinned with a large number of pins </strong>in a distance of 2-2.5 cm from each other. Then I stretch it along the whole pattern, pulling the mesh and constantly fixing it with pins. The mesh should be stretched not so tightly, so later when you remove pins, it will not be distorted. If you have a slight stretching, you will achieve a close fit of the garment to the clients’ body.</p><p><strong>Take the mock-up of the top, undo the sleeves, cut the embroidery including sequins together with the base and arrange it over the illusion mesh fabric. </strong>Please arrange the sequins in the correct direction. Regardless the smaller size of embroidered sleeves than on the pattern, they fit perfectly during the dress- fitting, so I do not need to redo anything.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2054.files/image004.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>Now I move on to the main issue – the alteration in the back of the top, which I need to make. </strong></p><p><strong>During the dress-fitting I saw that all fitted well, but there was no enough stretch in the armpit area to spread the top out. </strong>It is not a secret, that the armpit area is problematic, especially in dresses and open back tops. So, I decided to change the initial variant.&nbsp; <strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>The black line on pattern –</strong> is the initial line, along which I attach the mock-up of the top to the dress.</p><p><strong>Certainly, the easiest option to get rid of it is to prolong the pattern along the blue dotted line to the dress, to the lacing or in other words to make the back of dress less open.</strong></p><p>Neither me, nor my client are satisfied with such option of the closed back!</p><p><strong>Thus, it is necessary to find the option when the deficiencies are removed and the design of the back is kept to as planned! </strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2054.files/image006.jpg" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>At the beginning I decided to change the configuration of the back as shown on the pattern with red lines. </strong>I added a mesh triangle, which pulls this area and removes ripples.</p><p><strong>Although, in the final option shown on the pattern with green lines, </strong>I decided to move the triangle upper to cover all problematic area and to pull it to the center of the back.</p><p><strong>I think that such option will work out and the distortion in the armpit area will be eliminated!</strong></p><p><strong>I did the same with the second half of the top. &nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Thus, I drew a new back line, on which I need to add embroidery and additional triangle.</strong></p><p><strong>If your top is of nude color, you may leave this triangle without any embroidery </strong>as it will not be visible on body<strong>. &nbsp;</strong></p><p>I think that it is necessary to make sequin embroidery on the edges<strong> on white mesh fabric</strong> I use as I want to keep the initial idea.</p><p><strong>There is one more minor alteration I decided to make after the dress-fitting – I prolonged the back. </strong>On the new pattern you can see that the green line of triangle base goes lower the initial black line. I draw the new bottom line by placing dress on the pattern.</p><p><strong>These were the alterations I made to the initial pattern of top.</strong></p><p><strong>The most important is that you need to remember that the appearance of the top will depend on fabric you select. </strong>You need to choose the tender and fine fabrics. If you want to make embroidery on it, you will definitely need to embroider on something synthetic and then move embroidery on the top.</p><p><strong>I continue my work with the pattern of the top.</strong></p><p><strong>I find the exact center of embroidery cut out from the mock-up and glue it with the Gutermann glue.</strong></p><p><strong>You need to glue the rows of sequins starting from the center toward different direction. </strong>I pin the glue line on both sides to avoid moving mesh fabric and to fix it in required position.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2054.files/image008.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>If you want to stitch embroidery, </strong>I recommend fixing embroidery with glue points along the stitch and when the altered embroidery would be cut out and remove from the table you need to make hand stitches between the glue points, constantly stretching the mesh fabric. <strong>&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>I recommend gluing thin and narrow ribbon along the cuts of the front and the back of the top. In this case, </strong>I will be able to join my super elastic mesh fabric without distortions. Each small shift during joining will lead to ripples on the top.</p></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="pattern"><p>Sewing patterns are in PDF format. To print sewing patterns open the files, press “print” and choose&nbsp;<strong>“print in actual size”</strong>. In each&nbsp;file the pattern is divided &nbsp;to A4 paper sheets for home printers.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><strong>Automatic Pattern Alterations Calculator:</strong></h4><h4><strong><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/calculations/ENGcorset/corset.htm" target="_blank">The Dress (Corset)</a></strong></h4><h4><strong><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/calculations/ENGskirt/ENGskirt.htm" target="_blank">The Skirt</a></strong></h4><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p> <a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/belt%2C%20bow.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Belf and The Bow</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/corset%20-%20front.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> Corset Front</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/corset%20-%20lining.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> Corset Lining</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/pattern.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Pattern</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/skirt.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Skirt</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/top.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Top</a><br></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="diploma"><div class="dark-get-started margin-0"><p>In order to receive the Corset Academy graduation diploma you need to submit your graduation work.<br> Upload the photo of the garment that you made after completing the course.<br> I will personally review your work.<br> After the approval you will receive a personalized diploma to your email box, no longer than within 1 business day.</p><p class="text-right">Tatiana Kozorovitsky.</p><form id="diplomaForm"><h4>Your datails:</h4><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="firstname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter first name" required=""><p class="firstname error">Enter your first name</p></div><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="lastname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter last name" required=""><p class="lastname error">Enter your last name</p></div><h4>Choose a course:</h4><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option1" value="1"> <label for="option1"> <em>Wedding gowns design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option2" value="2"> <label for="option2"> <em>Evening dresses design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option3" value="3"> <label for="option3"> <em>Corsetry design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><p class="course error margin-10-bottom">Select course</p><div class="form-group"> <label class="uploadbutton"><div class="button">Choose file</div><div class="pull-left"><div class="input">No file selected</div></div> <input type="file" id="fileupload" name="files[]" data-url="https://corsetacademy.net/diploma/upload/"> </label><div id="progress" class="progress" style="display: none;"><div class="bar progress-bar progress-bar-warning progress-bar-striped active" role="progressbar" style="width: 0%;"></div></div> <input type="hidden" id="uploadDataUrl"><p class="upload error">Please upload photo of your work.</p><p>Max file size 2 Mb</p></div> <input type="hidden" id="userEmail" value="ngochuy.mmt@gmail.com"> <button id="submitDiploma" type="submit" class="btn btn-green-simple">Submit</button><h3 id="submitSpinner" class="text-center" style="display:none"><i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin"></i></h3></form><h4 id="statusAnswer" class="text-center"></h4><div class="clearfix"></div><h3 class="get-pro text-center">The example of the diploma:</h3> <a href="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/diploma_example.png" class="wplightbox" title="Diploma Example"><div id="diploma_example"></div> </a></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="faq"><p class="text-center"><i class="fa fa-spinner fa-pulse fa-3x"></i></p></div></div></div></div>

